{"lemma":"خَلْطُ","slug":"خَلْطُ","root":"خ.ل.ط","root_slug":"خ-ل-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ل-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَلْطُ","root":"خلط","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n11296","n11297","n11298","n11299","n11300"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix up, to confuse"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tell every secret to, to initiate in everything","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix well"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to confuse"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَلَطَ (ḵalaṭa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anything that blends into a mass, component of a mixture, admixture"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"humour in humourism"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Form II intensive of خَلَطَ (ḵalaṭa, “to mix”)."},"ipa":["/xa.la.tˤa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11296","headword_ar":"خَلْطٌ","root":"xlT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n11297","headword_ar":"خِلْطٌ","root":"xlT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that mixes, mingles, commingles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becomes incorporated"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blended, with a thing; an admixture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any kind of mixture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a medicinal mixture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaATN","text_ar":"اَخْلَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfume,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) pl. as above. (S, Msb.) ―         -b3-  [Sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxlAT","text_ar":"اخلاط"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the term]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaATu AlA_inosaAni","text_ar":"اَخْلَاطُ الاـِنْسَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The four humours of man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are the constituents of his composition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almir~ataAni","text_ar":"المِرَّتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the black bile and the yellow bile"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albalogamu","text_ar":"البَلْغَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the phlegm"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~amu","text_ar":"الدَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzj","text_ar":"مزج"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mixed dates of various sorts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (K.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who mixes with others, and manifests love to them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiloTapN","text_ar":"خِلْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does so:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) and the former, (IAar, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloTN","text_ar":"خَلْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this signifies [simply]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxaAliTN","text_ar":"مُخَالِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [see 3,] and is an inf. n. used in that sense, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliTN","text_ar":"خَلِطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluTN","text_ar":"خُلُطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is mentioned by Sb and explained by Seer, (TA,) (tropical:)  a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who mixes with others,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and manifests love to them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and behaves in a blandishing manner to them"},{"kind":"text","text":", and one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who casts his women and goods among men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliTapN","text_ar":"خَلِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in like manner, applied to a female. (TA.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mixed race:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bastard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN xiloTN miloTN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ خِلْطٌ مِلْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man of mixed race:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of faulty race:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloTN","text_ar":"مِلْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose race and father are unknown."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaATN mina Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"اَخْلَاطٌ مِنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A medley,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"promiscuous multitude"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collection, of men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the lowest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest sort,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"riffraff, thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyTN","text_ar":"خَلِيطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ibn-'Abbád, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~ayoTaY","text_ar":"خُلَّيْطَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xulayoTaY","text_ar":"خُلَيْطَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ibn-'Abbád, K:) to these ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahun~a","text_ar":"لَهُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahum","text_ar":"لَهُم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) there is no sing.: (K, TA:) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyTN","text_ar":"خَلِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a sing., and has pls., as will be seen below. (TA.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stupid; foolish; having little sense;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliTN","text_ar":"خَلِطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, Sgh, K:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaATN","text_ar":"اَخْلَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, TA;) with which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluTN","text_ar":"خُلُطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. (TA.) ―         -b8-  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crooked"},{"kind":"text","text":"bow, and arrow; (K;) an arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the wood has grown crookedly, and which ceases not to be crooked even if it have been straightened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiliTN","text_ar":"خِلِطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to either of these. (K.) And in like manner, (assumed tropical:)  a man; he being likened to such an arrow: and (assumed tropical:)  a people, or company of men. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","IAar","Lth","O","Sgh"]},{"entry_id":"n11298","headword_ar":"خَلِطٌ","root":"xlT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiloTN","text_ar":"خِلْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good in disposition; good-natured."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n11299","headword_ar":"خُلُطٌ","root":"xlT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiloTN","text_ar":"خِلْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b2-  [and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyTN","text_ar":"خَلِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is a pl.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n11300","headword_ar":"خِلِطٌ","root":"xlT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiloTN","text_ar":"خِلْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}